.TH "ad_sigma_delta_single_conversion" 9 "ad_sigma_delta_single_conversion" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ad_sigma_delta_single_conversion \- Performs a single data conversion
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ad_sigma_delta_single_conversion
.BI "(struct iio_dev *indio_dev "  ","
.BI "const struct iio_chan_spec *chan "  ","
.BI "int *val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "indio_dev" 12
The IIO device
.IP "chan" 12
The conversion is done for this channel
.IP "val" 12
Pointer to the location where to store the read value
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, an error value otherwise.
